===2020 census===
As of the [[2020 United States census|2020 census]], Miller had a population of 50, with 16 households and 10 families residing in the community. The [[population density]] was 24.2 inhabitants per square mile (9.3/km<sup>2</sup>). There were 26 housing units at an average density of 12.6 per square mile (4.9/km<sup>2</sup>).<ref name="Census2020DP">{{cite web|title=2020 Decennial Census Demographic Profile (DP1)|url=https://api.census.gov/data/2020/dec/dp?get=NAME,DP1_0021P,DP1_0024P,DP1_0025C,DP1_0049C,DP1_0045C,DP1_0069C,DP1_0073C,DP1_0125P,DP1_0126P,DP1_0129P,DP1_0133P,DP1_0137P,DP1_0138P,DP1_0139P,DP1_0141P,DP1_0142P,DP1_0143P,DP1_0145P,DP1_0146P,DP1_0147C,DP1_0148C,DP1_0149C,DP1_0156C,DP1_0157C,DP1_0158C,DP1_0159P,DP1_0160P&for=place%3A52140&in=state%3A19|website=United States Census Bureau|year=2021|access-date=May 2, 2026|df=mdy}}</ref>

Of the 16 households, 12.5% had children under the age of 18 living with them, 62.5% were [[Marriage|married couples]] living together, 0.0% were cohabitating couples, 6.2% had a female householder with no spouse or partner present, and 31.2% had a male householder with no spouse or partner present. About 37.5% of all households were non-families, 37.5% were made up of individuals, and 12.5% had someone living alone who was 65 years of age or older. There were 26 housing units, of which 38.5% were vacant. The homeowner vacancy rate was 0.0% and the rental vacancy rate was 100.0%.<ref name="Census2020DP"/>

The median age was 46.5 years. About 28.0% of residents were under the age of 20, 0.0% were from 20 to 24, 20.0% were from 25 to 44, 36.0% were from 45 to 64, and 16.0% were 65 years of age or older. The gender makeup of the community was 14.0% male and 86.0% female.<ref name="Census2020DP"/> All residents lived in rural areas.<ref name="Census2020DHC">{{cite web|title=2020 Decennial Census Demographic and Housing Characteristics (DHC)|url=https://api.census.gov/data/2020/dec/dhc?get=NAME,P2_002N,P2_003N&for=place%3A52140&in=state%3A19|website=United States Census Bureau|year=2023|access-date=May 2, 2026|df=mdy}}</ref>

